Using the go-cli, it appears that it strips all empty properties from a JSON object, here's the same action run with the go-cli:

```
ok: invoked /_/f with id ...
{
  "activationId": "...",
  "name": "f",
  "response": {
    "status": "success",
    "success": true
  }, ...
}
```

Notice the absence of `"logs": []` (also missing are `annotations and parameters`. So it's a feature with the new CLI but that doesn't help direct API users or the UI.

